00:27:54.790 --> 00:27:59.750 align:middle
Aah, you know, a scandal is
being covered up here, isn't it?

00:28:01.880 --> 00:28:03.290 align:middle
That's it!

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
B Komachi's Ai

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
has a set of

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
illegitimate

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
twins?!

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
Maternity Health-Record Book

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
Suspicious

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
maternity

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
health-record

00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
book

00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:07.460 align:middle
If I sold the story to a weekly magazine,
I could be swimming in cash...

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:11.130 align:middle
I don't give a crap what happens
anymore - I'm gonna do it!

00:28:11.790 --> 00:28:14.420 align:middle
Uh-oh, not good. What's the call? Do we kill her?

00:28:14.420 --> 00:28:17.250 align:middle
Not happening. She's got too much of a size advantage.

00:28:17.830 --> 00:28:21.210 align:middle
I was just kidding, but were you actually serious about it?

00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:24.210 align:middle
There's no question that this could
be trouble if we just let it be...

00:28:24.750 --> 00:28:25.670 align:middle
Even so...

00:28:28.250 --> 00:28:29.380 align:middle
What're we gonna do?!

00:28:29.500 --> 00:28:31.880 align:middle
She's snapping tons of pics of
the maternity health-record book!

00:28:32.210 --> 00:28:35.580 align:middle
Actually, I think this presents an opportunity.
I have an idea.

00:28:37.540 --> 00:28:42.210 align:middle
With the proceeds I get from selling this, I'll boost
my fave host to the top of the monthly rankings.

00:28:42.210 --> 00:28:43.630 align:middle
O wretched girl...

00:28:44.460 --> 00:28:47.790 align:middle
Thy heart's thirst cannot be quenched by champagne.

00:28:47.790 --> 00:28:48.790 align:middle
Who's there?!

00:28:52.500 --> 00:28:55.380 align:middle
I-I am a divine messenger.

00:28:56.210 --> 00:29:00.000 align:middle
Thy excesses... can no longer be overlooked.

00:29:01.000 --> 00:29:02.830 align:middle
A... "divine messenger"?

00:29:03.580 --> 00:29:07.170 align:middle
Wait a minute, that baby just talked... No way!

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:10.670 align:middle
In thy experience, are mere babes capable of speech?

00:29:10.670 --> 00:29:11.920 align:middle
Believe in me.

00:29:11.920 --> 00:29:15.170 align:middle
Well, it's just when you talk about the divine...

00:29:15.290 --> 00:29:17.460 align:middle
I don't believe in that kind of stuff...

00:29:17.960 --> 00:29:19.670 align:middle
Oh, I get it!

00:29:19.670 --> 00:29:24.250 align:middle
This must be a candid-camera thing! Like, some TV show
Ai-san is in where they prank the managers!

00:29:24.250 --> 00:29:25.170 align:middle
Those are totally a thing!

00:29:25.420 --> 00:29:29.540 align:middle
They sure went to a lot of trouble.
There's a camera somewhere around here, right?

00:29:29.540 --> 00:29:32.290 align:middle
Tch... I guess this was too much of a stretch.

00:29:32.830 --> 00:29:36.380 align:middle
Now, now, Ruby-chan,
it's dangerous up there on the tab-

00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:40.380 align:middle
Behave thyself! I am an incarnation of Amaterasu.

00:29:41.170 --> 00:29:43.040 align:middle
I am what ye call a god.

00:29:44.750 --> 00:29:45.540 align:middle
"God"...

00:29:46.210 --> 00:29:48.630 align:middle
Manipulated by prospects of immediate profit,

00:29:48.830 --> 00:29:51.000 align:middle
thou art on the verge of abandoning thy destiny.

00:29:51.420 --> 00:29:52.580 align:middle
My destiny...?

00:29:53.250 --> 00:29:56.500 align:middle
Ai Hoshino was chosen by the God of Entertainment.

00:29:56.790 --> 00:30:01.290 align:middle
Furthermore, those children are twins
who bear a monumental destiny.

00:30:01.790 --> 00:30:05.580 align:middle
It is thy destiny to keep guard over them.

00:30:06.170 --> 00:30:08.710 align:middle
Thy deeds run contrary to the will of the gods.

00:30:09.460 --> 00:30:11.790 align:middle
Should thou not desist, divine punishment
shall be visited upon thee.

00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:13.080 align:middle
"Divine punishment"?!

00:30:13.380 --> 00:30:16.130 align:middle
What do you mean that?! In concrete terms...!

00:30:16.130 --> 00:30:19.250 align:middle
In concrete terms? Specifically...

00:30:19.460 --> 00:30:20.250 align:middle
Thou shalt perish.

00:30:20.540 --> 00:30:21.750 align:middle
Yes, perish!

00:30:22.000 --> 00:30:22.960 align:middle
No!

00:30:22.960 --> 00:30:24.750 align:middle
That's super concrete!

00:30:24.750 --> 00:30:28.130 align:middle
What... should I do?

00:30:29.460 --> 00:30:30.920 align:middle
It is simply, really.

00:30:31.380 --> 00:30:34.290 align:middle
Guard the secret of their mother and us.

00:30:34.790 --> 00:30:39.460 align:middle
Moreover, dote on these children
and do everything they ask of thee.

00:30:39.460 --> 00:30:40.540 align:middle
"Everything"...

00:30:40.750 --> 00:30:46.130 align:middle
Handsome

00:30:40.750 --> 00:30:46.130 align:middle
man

00:30:40.960 --> 00:30:45.040 align:middle
Do thusly, and a second marriage to a
handsome actor is not out of the question.

00:30:45.040 --> 00:30:46.130 align:middle
Seriously?!

00:30:46.540 --> 00:30:48.750 align:middle
I'll do it! I'll do whatever is asked of me!

00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.920 align:middle
I'll even lick their insoles if need be!

00:30:50.920 --> 00:30:52.420 align:middle
Thou needn't go that far.

00:30:55.040 --> 00:30:57.290 align:middle
A second marriage to a handsome guy~

00:30:59.920 --> 00:31:01.630 align:middle
Do you think that was the right call?

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:04.920 align:middle
At any rate, there is a limit to infants' scope of activities.

00:31:05.460 --> 00:31:07.290 align:middle
And now we'll able to go outside.

00:31:07.290 --> 00:31:08.250 align:middle
Yay!

00:31:08.880 --> 00:31:12.460 align:middle
You know... that was quite a convincing performance.

00:31:12.880 --> 00:31:14.750 align:middle
Did you do theater before?

00:31:14.750 --> 00:31:16.830 align:middle
Nope, this was a first for me.

00:31:17.290 --> 00:31:20.460 align:middle
A first? You never put on any plays at school?

00:31:21.290 --> 00:31:24.630 align:middle
Well, I was raised in a bit of an usual place...

00:31:25.080 --> 00:31:26.080 align:middle
Hmm?

00:31:26.080 --> 00:31:27.540 align:middle
I guess it's just talent, then.

00:31:27.920 --> 00:31:29.500 align:middle
Maybe you'll be an actress in the future.

00:31:31.210 --> 00:31:32.500 align:middle
My future...

00:31:34.750 --> 00:31:36.710 align:middle
I've never given it any thought.

00:31:42.920 --> 00:31:44.790 align:middle
I found myself with a little sister.

00:31:45.750 --> 00:31:47.960 align:middle
A strange gal who is an idol otaku.

00:31:49.380 --> 00:31:50.250 align:middle
That said...

00:31:52.130 --> 00:31:56.790 align:middle
So, Ai-chan... She dances so nimbly!
And her charisma is off the charts!

00:31:57.170 --> 00:31:57.960 align:middle
Hmm...

00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:01.420 align:middle
I like Ai-chan the best of anyone in the whole world,

00:32:01.790 --> 00:32:04.710 align:middle
but I like you just about as much, Sensei!

00:32:05.500 --> 00:32:08.210 align:middle
The passion this girl has when she talks about Ai...

00:32:09.290 --> 00:32:10.960 align:middle
is just like yours...

00:32:11.790 --> 00:32:12.580 align:middle
Sarina-chan.

00:32:14.500 --> 00:32:16.330 align:middle
What? Did you call for me?

00:32:16.330 --> 00:32:17.960 align:middle
My bad, did I wake you up?

00:32:18.420 --> 00:32:19.960 align:middle
I wasn't calling out to you.

00:32:20.750 --> 00:32:22.960 align:middle
If you're gonna sleep, go to your bed.

00:32:29.830 --> 00:32:31.540 align:middle
Well, yeah.

00:32:33.670 --> 00:32:35.420 align:middle
There's no way he was...

00:32:37.330 --> 00:32:39.540 align:middle
After all, Sarina was my name in my previous life.

00:32:41.960 --> 00:32:45.290 align:middle
It has been a few months since
Ai returned to being an idol.

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle
Surging in popularity!            New Release

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle
Sign wa B

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle
New Release!!

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:49.920 align:middle
B Komachi

00:32:46.080 --> 00:32:49.040 align:middle
And, well, the steady rise of B Komachi...

00:32:49.920 --> 00:32:52.880 align:middle
Net Pay

00:32:50.130 --> 00:32:52.290 align:middle
did not materialize.

00:32:53.130 --> 00:32:55.580 align:middle
My pay this month is 200,000 yen...

00:32:56.170 --> 00:32:59.330 align:middle
Hey, this agency's so stingy with pay.

00:32:59.750 --> 00:33:02.750 align:middle
The single we just put out reached
no. 3 on the Oricon charts, didn't it?

00:33:03.170 --> 00:33:04.750 align:middle
Aren't the middlemen taking too big a cut?

00:33:05.170 --> 00:33:06.790 align:middle
Complaining only just now?

00:33:06.790 --> 00:33:11.750 align:middle
Unlike the big players who do everything from
production to distribution, we're a puny talent agency.

00:33:12.290 --> 00:33:14.630 align:middle
You came into this knowing our profits are slim, right?

00:33:15.130 --> 00:33:17.920 align:middle
I've finally realized the world revolves around money.

00:33:18.380 --> 00:33:20.250 align:middle
That's quite a depressing realization.

00:33:20.580 --> 00:33:22.710 align:middle
Being an idol is fun,

00:33:23.040 --> 00:33:27.040 align:middle
so I wouldn't mind going on like this if were just me.

00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:32.830 align:middle
But, I want to send these kids to good schools
and have them take lessons and so on.

00:33:33.210 --> 00:33:39.710 align:middle
To give them lots of options, I've gotta sell better
and earn as much as possible, don't I?

00:33:40.580 --> 00:33:44.580 align:middle
As things stand now, I won't be able
to make these kids happy.

00:33:47.960 --> 00:33:52.130 align:middle
Aww, I sure wish I'd get some job offers
for commercials or films...

00:33:52.130 --> 00:33:53.710 align:middle
Now, if I were with a major agency...

00:33:54.380 --> 00:33:57.040 align:middle
Well, lay off that pricey ice cream for a start.

00:34:00.670 --> 00:34:02.380 align:middle
I'm heading off for my lesson.

00:34:03.750 --> 00:34:05.380 align:middle
Be good while Mommy's gone, okay?

00:34:09.250 --> 00:34:13.000 align:middle
Hey, don't idols usually make
like one million yen a month?

00:34:13.290 --> 00:34:14.670 align:middle
Far from it.

00:34:14.670 --> 00:34:15.920 align:middle
Wait, they don't?!

00:34:16.040 --> 00:34:20.750 align:middle
Oshi-Dol

00:34:16.330 --> 00:34:20.750 align:middle
Song royalties and TV appearance fees
are split between the members...

00:34:21.080 --> 00:34:24.080 align:middle
Concerts come out in the red
if the merch doesn't sell well.

00:34:24.500 --> 00:34:26.580 align:middle
And clothing expenses are deducted from their pay.

00:34:27.330 --> 00:34:29.670 align:middle
Only a select handful pull in one million a month.

00:34:29.670 --> 00:34:34.210 align:middle
What the hell?! The world's beyond saving when
money doesn't reach the people giving it their all!

00:34:34.750 --> 00:34:35.960 align:middle
Oh, I know!

00:34:36.500 --> 00:34:41.420 align:middle
All the otaku could take turns offering
up their livers to Ai, which we'll sell...

00:34:41.420 --> 00:34:43.630 align:middle
That idea of yours is beyond saving...

00:34:43.880 --> 00:34:47.330 align:middle
Cut it out with that post-nuclear-holocaust
view of religion.

00:34:48.540 --> 00:34:51.460 align:middle
She sings and dances, and her face is out of this world...

00:34:51.960 --> 00:34:53.750 align:middle
She does lessons and vocal training...

00:34:53.750 --> 00:34:56.380 align:middle
And she's a hard worker who practices
choreography at home at night.

00:34:56.880 --> 00:34:59.830 align:middle
B Komachi is one of the better-selling groups, and yet...

00:35:02.380 --> 00:35:03.710 align:middle
Hey, manager!

00:35:04.040 --> 00:35:06.170 align:middle
Why isn't our Ai getting any job offers?!

00:35:06.170 --> 00:35:09.330 align:middle
What crap management!
Put more effort into sales and marketing!

00:35:09.750 --> 00:35:11.710 align:middle
Easier said than done...

00:35:12.420 --> 00:35:16.250 align:middle
In the end, with idol groups
you have a business situation where

00:35:16.250 --> 00:35:20.420 align:middle
dozens of people cluster together only to compete
for jobs with solo entertainers, you see.

00:35:21.130 --> 00:35:24.500 align:middle
And when they can finally secure jobs
when sold as a set package,

00:35:24.500 --> 00:35:28.420 align:middle
if one tries to compete as a solo performer,
there's a high hurdle to clear.

00:35:28.420 --> 00:35:32.130 align:middle
Super Popular

00:35:28.420 --> 00:35:32.130 align:middle
Idol Group       Graduation!

00:35:28.790 --> 00:35:32.290 align:middle
Despite graduating from their idol groups
due to a desire to do solo work,

00:35:32.290 --> 00:35:34.040 align:middle
they are tons of ex-idols who,

00:35:34.040 --> 00:35:37.170 align:middle
unable to secure jobs on their own, work at high-end
food and drink establishments in Roppongi

00:35:37.170 --> 00:35:42.420 align:middle
or become Minato girls scraping by via getting
paid to go out drinking, you know?

00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:44.290 align:middle
I actually don't know...

00:35:44.290 --> 00:35:46.250 align:middle
Tokyo's a scary place.

00:35:46.630 --> 00:35:49.080 align:middle
I do admit that Ai is amazing.

00:35:49.540 --> 00:35:52.750 align:middle
But that only extends to within the idol sphere.

00:35:53.880 --> 00:35:55.420 align:middle
In the entertainment industry,

00:35:55.420 --> 00:35:59.540 align:middle
you can't make it unless you have something special
that allows you to compete all on your own.

00:36:00.170 --> 00:36:04.250 align:middle
A highly profitable job is not one that
requests "somebody from B Komachi" -

00:36:04.250 --> 00:36:07.000 align:middle
it is one that specifically requests Ai.

00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:12.380 align:middle
Being first-class as an idol is on its own not enough.

00:36:21.750 --> 00:36:23.790 align:middle
Ai-chan, are you feeling a bit down?

00:36:24.130 --> 00:36:27.210 align:middle
You've only just recovered,
so don't push yourself too hard, 'kay?

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:33.040 align:middle
It's nothing like that. It's just I missed lunch
and I'm starving now!

00:36:33.040 --> 00:36:34.830 align:middle
What?! You some big eater all of a sudden?!

00:36:36.920 --> 00:36:38.210 align:middle
Let's go over that last part again.

00:36:38.210 --> 00:36:39.000 align:middle
Okay!

00:36:39.000 --> 00:36:40.790 align:middle
I'm not feeling up to this today...

00:36:41.830 --> 00:36:43.040 align:middle
Guess I'll do some egosurfing.

00:36:45.420 --> 00:36:48.420 align:middle
Tanujirou

00:36:45.420 --> 00:36:48.420 align:middle
For better or worse, Ai's smile is that of a pro.

00:36:45.420 --> 00:36:48.420 align:middle
It's like it lacks human feeling...

00:36:45.420 --> 00:36:48.420 align:middle
I can't fully support her.

00:36:51.750 --> 00:36:53.960 align:middle
Hitting me where it hurts...

00:36:57.790 --> 00:36:59.500 align:middle
Congratulations on

00:36:57.790 --> 00:36:59.500 align:middle
the Performance

00:36:57.790 --> 00:36:59.500 align:middle
B Komachi

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.210 align:middle
B Komachi

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.210 align:middle
Ai's fan for

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.210 align:middle
all eternity

00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:02.460 align:middle
A sales promo event! A mini concert!

00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:05.790 align:middle
The kind you need to win a ticket lottery for!

00:37:07.330 --> 00:37:10.420 align:middle
This will be my first time truly seeing Mama perform live.

00:37:10.830 --> 00:37:12.000 align:middle
Now, listen here.

00:37:12.790 --> 00:37:15.290 align:middle
I brought you here since you kept insisting,

00:37:15.290 --> 00:37:18.830 align:middle
but I'm the one who'll take the brunt of it
if the president finds out about this, got it?

00:37:19.210 --> 00:37:21.920 align:middle
B Komachi

00:37:19.210 --> 00:37:21.920 align:middle
Ai's fan for

00:37:19.210 --> 00:37:21.920 align:middle
all eternity

00:37:19.830 --> 00:37:21.920 align:middle
No cheering, running, or speaking!

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:24.790 align:middle
Put in your pacifiers and behave yourselves, okay?

00:37:26.130 --> 00:37:27.540 align:middle
That's right, Ruby.

00:37:27.540 --> 00:37:30.500 align:middle
We absolutely can't do anything that makes us stand out.

00:37:31.960 --> 00:37:34.750 align:middle
Anything that gives a whiff of us being connected to Ai is-

00:37:34.750 --> 00:37:36.130 align:middle
I get it, okay?

00:37:37.130 --> 00:37:40.330 align:middle
You saw it too, right?
The way Mama was down in the dumps...

00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:43.830 align:middle
I'm here because I'm worried about her.

00:37:44.630 --> 00:37:47.040 align:middle
Please understand I didn't come to have fun.

00:37:45.250 --> 00:37:49.540 align:middle
Today, we have three members of B Komachi with us!

00:37:58.040 --> 00:38:04.420 align:middle
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

00:38:04.420 --> 00:38:06.080 align:middle
B Komachi! Woo-hoo!

00:38:07.290 --> 00:38:08.540 align:middle
B Komachi! Woo-hoo!

00:38:08.330 --> 00:38:11.580 align:middle
For better or worse, Ai's smile is that of a pro.

00:38:08.330 --> 00:38:11.580 align:middle
It's like it lacks human feeling...

00:38:08.340 --> 00:38:11.580 align:middle
I can't fully support her.

00:38:11.880 --> 00:38:15.830 align:middle
They can go and say that... After all, I am a professional.

00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:20.460 align:middle
It's like it lacks human feeling...

00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:20.460 align:middle
I can't fully support her.

00:38:17.170 --> 00:38:19.500 align:middle
Besides, I don't really get it.

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:23.000 align:middle
You're the ones who want something almost inhuman.

00:38:23.750 --> 00:38:27.290 align:middle
I look in the mirror and study it.
I fine tune it to the millimeter.

00:38:27.830 --> 00:38:30.420 align:middle
The way I narrow my eyes, the corners of my mouth..

00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:31.540 align:middle
It's all calculated.

00:38:32.080 --> 00:38:35.290 align:middle
I'm always putting on the smile that
will please people the most.

00:38:36.290 --> 00:38:39.500 align:middle
I am... made up of lies, after all.

00:38:41.710 --> 00:38:49.960 align:middle
Goo-goo! Ga-ga! Goo-goo! Ga-ga! Goo-goo! Ga-ga!

00:38:44.920 --> 00:38:46.330 align:middle
What's with those babies?!

00:38:46.330 --> 00:38:47.880 align:middle
They're doing an idol-fan dance!

00:38:47.880 --> 00:38:49.830 align:middle
And with such skill I can't believe they're infants!

00:38:50.290 --> 00:38:54.540 align:middle
You came 'cause you were worried, huh?! Looks to me
like you're enjoying this more than anyone else!

00:38:54.830 --> 00:38:56.500 align:middle
Instinct took over...!

00:38:57.670 --> 00:38:58.500 align:middle
Wow...

00:38:58.500 --> 00:39:00.420 align:middle
What the...? Amazing!

00:39:03.000 --> 00:39:06.790 align:middle
My kids are so cuuute!

00:39:08.040 --> 00:39:11.750 align:middle
Faced with the extraordinary sight of baby twins performing

00:39:08.040 --> 00:39:11.750 align:middle
an idol-fan dance, idol ends up spontaneously reacting

00:39:08.880 --> 00:39:11.500 align:middle
Two hundred ten thousand retweets...

00:39:12.210 --> 00:39:15.080 align:middle
And the reposted video already has two million views.

00:39:15.420 --> 00:39:20.000 align:middle
I get that it's easier for content
with babies to go viral, but still...

00:39:20.330 --> 00:39:22.250 align:middle
Let's have a little talk.

00:39:24.580 --> 00:39:25.790 align:middle
Anonymous

00:39:24.580 --> 00:39:25.790 align:middle
What's this girl's name?

00:39:25.790 --> 00:39:27.330 align:middle
Anonymous

00:39:25.790 --> 00:39:27.330 align:middle
Wait, did Ai always smile like this?

00:39:25.790 --> 00:39:27.330 align:middle
My impression of her has changed a bit.

00:39:28.250 --> 00:39:29.540 align:middle
Anonymous

00:39:28.250 --> 00:39:29.540 align:middle
I get nothing but

00:39:28.250 --> 00:39:29.540 align:middle
"troublesome otaku" vibes from these babies

00:39:32.500 --> 00:39:35.460 align:middle
Tanujirou

00:39:32.500 --> 00:39:35.460 align:middle
This right here! This is it!

00:39:33.880 --> 00:39:35.080 align:middle
Oh, I see...

00:39:35.710 --> 00:39:37.710 align:middle
So this is good, huh?

00:39:38.830 --> 00:39:41.080 align:middle
I'll remember that.

00:39:43.670 --> 00:39:45.080 align:middle
One year has passed since then.

00:39:45.630 --> 00:39:50.420 align:middle
We've grown to the point where it is no longer
suspicious for us to walk around or talk,

00:39:50.880 --> 00:39:51.750 align:middle
and my sister...

00:39:51.750 --> 00:39:53.130 align:middle
Mama! Mama!

00:39:53.750 --> 00:39:54.670 align:middle
Hm?

00:39:55.580 --> 00:39:57.330 align:middle
Pat me!

00:39:57.710 --> 00:39:59.170 align:middle
Pat, pat~

00:39:59.630 --> 00:40:04.290 align:middle
has superbly embodied a zealous fan who clings
to their idol and brands them "Mama."

00:40:04.670 --> 00:40:08.040 align:middle
Aww, Pure Land of Perfect Bliss.

00:40:08.580 --> 00:40:11.790 align:middle
Where'd you learn a difficult phrase like that?

00:40:12.790 --> 00:40:13.790 align:middle
Wait, could it be that you...

00:40:15.290 --> 00:40:16.960 align:middle
Well, I...

00:40:17.460 --> 00:40:20.460 align:middle
Could it be that Ai finds us suspicious in...

00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:22.750 align:middle
...are like some kinda super genius?

00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:27.080 align:middle
...no way at all, so we spend peaceful days together.

00:40:27.380 --> 00:40:28.380 align:middle
Must be genetic!

00:40:30.920 --> 00:40:32.920 align:middle
From model to radio assistant...

00:40:33.420 --> 00:40:35.630 align:middle
Ai steadily picked up more gigs,

00:40:35.630 --> 00:40:38.920 align:middle
and today she has a job that could be said
to be the crystallization of all that work.

00:40:39.670 --> 00:40:41.830 align:middle
Mama, your first TV drama - what fun!

00:40:42.170 --> 00:40:43.830 align:middle
It's only a minor role, though.

00:40:45.580 --> 00:40:47.330 align:middle
Now listen here, you two.

00:40:47.670 --> 00:40:50.670 align:middle
You kept insisting, so I brought you along,

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:55.170 align:middle
but make absolutely sure not to
call Ai-san "Mama" on the set, okay?

00:40:55.580 --> 00:40:58.630 align:middle
Don't forget that the story is that you're my kids.

00:40:58.880 --> 00:41:01.710 align:middle
Yeah, yeah. Mama, Mama, gimme some head pats.

00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:03.210 align:middle
Me too, Mama!

00:41:03.210 --> 00:41:05.420 align:middle
Mama, gimme my allowance.

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:11.000 align:middle
I'm Ai from Strawberry Productions.
I look forward to working with you today.

00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:12.710 align:middle
Same to you!

00:41:24.000 --> 00:41:25.960 align:middle
Is something the matter, Director?

00:41:25.960 --> 00:41:27.170 align:middle
No, nothing in particular.

00:41:27.170 --> 00:41:28.500 align:middle
Kinda scary, isn't he?

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:29.420 align:middle
Yeah, that face of his.

00:41:29.750 --> 00:41:31.710 align:middle
Hm? Whose kids are these?

00:41:31.710 --> 00:41:33.630 align:middle
Oh, they're my kids.

00:41:34.040 --> 00:41:36.880 align:middle
The idea of a manager bringing her kids to the set...

00:41:40.540 --> 00:41:42.080 align:middle
This one of those work-style reform things?

00:41:42.330 --> 00:41:43.000 align:middle
Um?

00:41:43.000 --> 00:41:44.630 align:middle
Sign of the times, huh?

00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:47.580 align:middle
Well, some people even bring their dogs these days.

00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:52.290 align:middle
Yes, that won't be a problem. Huh?

00:41:50.250 --> 00:41:51.460 align:middle
Hey, we've also got some snacks.

00:41:51.460 --> 00:41:53.000 align:middle
So I was found out, huh?

00:41:52.290 --> 00:41:53.750 align:middle
My children are very well behaved, you see.

00:41:53.130 --> 00:41:54.670 align:middle
I'm on a diet.

00:41:53.880 --> 00:41:56.130 align:middle
Twins! How cute!

00:41:56.420 --> 00:41:59.080 align:middle
Oh, if I recall, this girl's a pinup model...

00:41:59.420 --> 00:42:02.960 align:middle
And that one's an young performer who's called
"an adorable actress with real acting chops."

00:42:03.130 --> 00:42:04.920 align:middle
Goo-goo! Ga-ga!

00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:06.460 align:middle
Knock it off with that cutie-pie act.

00:42:07.460 --> 00:42:09.710 align:middle
It's no use. My body's giving out.

00:42:11.790 --> 00:42:12.460 align:middle
Hm?

00:42:14.290 --> 00:42:16.040 align:middle
Oh, you're that manager's kid.

00:42:16.880 --> 00:42:21.250 align:middle
I don't mind you being here, but if you cry
and interrupt the filming, I'll kick you out.

00:42:21.250 --> 00:42:23.540 align:middle
Oh, we'd never!

00:42:23.540 --> 00:42:26.210 align:middle
Though we may be a babies, we shall strive
to not make any such blunders!

00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:30.290 align:middle
I am well aware that not hindering
the production process is a baseline rule.

00:42:30.290 --> 00:42:33.500 align:middle
Please show favor to our agency's Ai going forward.

00:42:33.500 --> 00:42:35.670 align:middle
Whoa, this baby sure is talkative!

00:42:35.880 --> 00:42:37.710 align:middle
Where'd you learn all those words?!

00:42:37.710 --> 00:42:39.790 align:middle
Here and there on YouTube...

00:42:39.790 --> 00:42:42.710 align:middle
Man, that YouTube is amazing! Sign of the times, huh?!

00:42:43.380 --> 00:42:47.750 align:middle
I see a good number of precocious child actors,
but you're really something else.

00:42:48.250 --> 00:42:50.080 align:middle
You do any acting by chance?

00:42:50.330 --> 00:42:52.670 align:middle
No, acting and such isn't something I...

00:42:53.130 --> 00:42:57.130 align:middle
You'd be interesting up on screen.
I'd like to put you in something.

00:42:58.040 --> 00:42:59.540 align:middle
Here's my business card.

00:42:59.920 --> 00:43:01.920 align:middle
Give me a call if you sign up with an agency.

00:43:01.920 --> 00:43:06.210 align:middle
No, if you're going to hand out work,
then give it to Ai rather than me.

00:43:06.210 --> 00:43:08.080 align:middle
Oh, that idol...

00:43:08.540 --> 00:43:12.380 align:middle
She has an exceptional face.
With some luck, she'll survive in the industry.

00:43:09.250 --> 00:43:10.420 align:middle
This looks delicious!

00:43:12.920 --> 00:43:15.130 align:middle
She needs luck despite having an exceptional face?

00:43:15.130 --> 00:43:18.040 align:middle
Listen here, kid. There are three types of actors.

00:43:18.500 --> 00:43:19.920 align:middle
Look at them over there.

00:43:20.630 --> 00:43:22.210 align:middle
One is the star actor.

00:43:22.500 --> 00:43:25.460 align:middle
Their primary role is to attract an audience.

00:43:25.830 --> 00:43:29.000 align:middle
Given they also act as poster children,
they garner solid performance fees.

00:43:29.210 --> 00:43:33.330 align:middle
Next is those with real talent. Their role is
to ensure the quality of the product on screen.

00:43:33.630 --> 00:43:36.210 align:middle
Maintaining the programing block's brand is their job.

00:43:36.790 --> 00:43:41.250 align:middle
Lastly, you've got newcomer actors.
Acting ability isn't really expected from them.

00:43:41.580 --> 00:43:44.500 align:middle
They get a passing mark if they can bring
a sense of freshness to the screen.

00:43:45.330 --> 00:43:48.330 align:middle
There's also the goal of giving
the next stars some experience.

00:43:48.670 --> 00:43:51.250 align:middle
I suppose it's an investment the entire industry makes.

00:43:52.040 --> 00:43:56.880 align:middle
In other words, all those fresh faces over
there are currently being invested in.

00:43:57.250 --> 00:43:59.540 align:middle
Unless they either draw in viewers
or become well-liked on set,

00:43:59.540 --> 00:44:02.830 align:middle
their places will be taken by the next crop of newcomers.

00:44:03.630 --> 00:44:08.960 align:middle
It would be a great success if even one of
the newcomers here today makes it in the industry.

00:44:09.290 --> 00:44:10.500 align:middle
That's the kind of world this is.

00:44:11.960 --> 00:44:14.580 align:middle
Those who survive are first-class at something or other.

00:44:14.580 --> 00:44:17.380 align:middle
Hmm... Well, she'll be fine, then.

00:44:17.830 --> 00:44:19.960 align:middle
Ai is a first-class idol.

00:44:20.170 --> 00:44:22.880 align:middle
No, even being a first-class idol won't cut it.

00:44:23.880 --> 00:44:24.670 align:middle
Director!

00:44:24.670 --> 00:44:26.210 align:middle
We're all ready for the set test.

00:44:26.210 --> 00:44:28.170 align:middle
Okay, I'll watch from here.

00:44:29.380 --> 00:44:30.460 align:middle
Ready and...!

00:44:31.960 --> 00:44:33.460 align:middle
What're you saying?

00:44:33.460 --> 00:44:35.500 align:middle
Want me to ask Touma-kun for you?

00:44:35.500 --> 00:44:37.170 align:middle
Hey! Don't even think about it!

00:44:39.040 --> 00:44:40.670 align:middle
But aren't you two always together?

00:44:40.670 --> 00:44:44.040 align:middle
Her acting is average...
but she really attracts your attention.

00:44:44.210 --> 00:44:46.380 align:middle
Right? She was talking about that earlier.

00:44:47.330 --> 00:44:52.040 align:middle
Up on stage, I need to look cute for everyone
no matter what angle they view me from,

00:44:53.040 --> 00:44:54.500 align:middle
but here it's only a single person...

00:44:55.000 --> 00:44:57.420 align:middle
I just need the camera to think I'm cute.

00:44:57.790 --> 00:45:01.290 align:middle
If the same tricks I use for music videos
will work, it's right in my wheelhouse.

00:45:01.500 --> 00:45:02.880 align:middle
Way to go!

00:45:02.880 --> 00:45:04.880 align:middle
I'll be cheering you on, okay?!

00:45:03.880 --> 00:45:07.460 align:middle
She thinks of it like a music video...
Sign of the times, huh?

00:45:07.460 --> 00:45:11.000 align:middle
What?! They're super well-made,
so you should really give them a look!

00:45:11.000 --> 00:45:12.750 align:middle
I'll even lend you the DVDs!

00:45:12.750 --> 00:45:13.880 align:middle
Keep it down, will ya?

00:45:18.790 --> 00:45:19.750 align:middle
It's still too soon.

00:45:20.170 --> 00:45:22.540 align:middle
It's never too late to take on a challenge.

00:45:21.580 --> 00:45:23.420 align:middle
I can't wait to see your performance, Mama!

00:45:23.420 --> 00:45:25.250 align:middle
Well, they did film me quite a bit.

00:45:25.710 --> 00:45:26.630 align:middle
Here it comes.

00:45:27.420 --> 00:45:28.460 align:middle
It's starting!

00:45:29.420 --> 00:45:30.790 align:middle
You in a bad mood or something?

00:45:30.790 --> 00:45:31.790 align:middle
Not really.

00:45:32.080 --> 00:45:33.290 align:middle
Was it something I did?

00:45:33.290 --> 00:45:34.170 align:middle
I said no!

00:45:33.290 --> 00:45:34.420 align:middle
Oh, this is the scene!

00:45:34.630 --> 00:45:35.580 align:middle
What is this?

00:45:36.290 --> 00:45:37.500 align:middle
Aww, it's Mama!

00:45:36.830 --> 00:45:37.630 align:middle
Good morning.

00:45:37.630 --> 00:45:39.250 align:middle
C'mon, give her a close-up!

00:45:37.920 --> 00:45:39.130 align:middle
Oh, good morning.

00:45:39.380 --> 00:45:40.790 align:middle
Huh? Is something wrong?

00:45:40.790 --> 00:45:42.380 align:middle
Wait! Touma!

00:45:43.210 --> 00:45:44.380 align:middle
You... Why're you here?

00:45:44.380 --> 00:45:46.380 align:middle
And that's why we weren't supposed to see each other.

00:45:47.500 --> 00:45:49.790 align:middle
Um, what do you mean by that?

00:45:51.580 --> 00:45:52.040 align:middle
News

00:45:52.210 --> 00:45:53.750 align:middle
What?! That's all?!

00:45:53.750 --> 00:45:54.170 align:middle
News

00:45:54.750 --> 00:45:56.630 align:middle
Just a bit of a single scene?!

00:45:56.630 --> 00:45:58.130 align:middle
They cut way too much!

00:45:58.540 --> 00:46:01.040 align:middle
I wonder if my acting was bad...

00:46:01.040 --> 00:46:03.130 align:middle
No, it definitely wasn't.

00:46:03.130 --> 00:46:05.580 align:middle
Yakitori

00:46:05.920 --> 00:46:06.710 align:middle
Yes?

00:46:06.710 --> 00:46:08.920 align:middle
Hey, Director, what's the big idea?!

00:46:09.290 --> 00:46:11.290 align:middle
Oh, hey, precocious baby.

00:46:11.710 --> 00:46:13.630 align:middle
You didn't give Ai any screen time!

00:46:14.040 --> 00:46:15.380 align:middle
Yeah, about that...

00:46:15.670 --> 00:46:18.080 align:middle
Her part came out great, so it's quite a shame.

00:46:18.080 --> 00:46:19.670 align:middle
Well, why then?!

00:46:20.130 --> 00:46:24.960 align:middle
The lead actress's agency promotes her as
"an adorable actress with real acting chops."

00:46:25.670 --> 00:46:29.210 align:middle
So how's it look when a girl with
an even prettier face is sharing the screen?

00:46:29.630 --> 00:46:31.710 align:middle
It'd be a problem for their image strategy, right?

00:46:32.500 --> 00:46:35.790 align:middle
Ai simply appeared too cute up on screen.

00:46:36.630 --> 00:46:42.290 align:middle
And so, word came down from the top to cut her
out as much as possible during editing.

00:46:42.580 --> 00:46:43.500 align:middle
Good grief...

00:46:43.750 --> 00:46:48.000 align:middle
The screen time a performer receives tends to be
decided by the power balance between companies,

00:46:48.000 --> 00:46:49.960 align:middle
so just see it as an unexpected misfortune and accept it.

00:46:50.330 --> 00:46:51.710 align:middle
I can't accept it.

00:46:55.830 --> 00:46:58.000 align:middle
It's fine to dream of the entertainment industry,

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:01.170 align:middle
but it's best not to have illusions
about the entertainment industry.

00:47:01.580 --> 00:47:04.380 align:middle
This isn't a place for art, but rather one for business.

00:47:05.040 --> 00:47:08.830 align:middle
But that said, I understand your point,
and I feel bad about this.

00:47:09.330 --> 00:47:11.580 align:middle
Mama, I know you did your very best!

00:47:10.080 --> 00:47:14.040 align:middle
I hesitate to say "in exchange,"
but I'd like to offer Ai another job.

00:47:11.790 --> 00:47:13.290 align:middle
I suppose I did.

00:47:14.670 --> 00:47:15.790 align:middle
For a film, that is.

00:47:15.790 --> 00:47:17.000 align:middle
Can't complain about that, right?

00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:17.880 align:middle
Seriously?!

00:47:17.880 --> 00:47:18.920 align:middle
On the condition that...

00:47:20.130 --> 00:47:22.500 align:middle
you also appear in the film.

00:47:24.880 --> 00:47:26.380 align:middle
Listen up, Precocious Baby.

00:47:26.960 --> 00:47:31.500 align:middle
In Japan, casting is for the most part
decided upon by the higher-ups.

00:47:32.790 --> 00:47:35.960 align:middle
The bigger the budget for a project,
the less it can afford to flop.

00:47:35.960 --> 00:47:38.830 align:middle
In order to secure actors who are sure to draw viewers,

00:47:38.830 --> 00:47:40.670 align:middle
the higher-ups have their own battles to fight.

00:47:41.210 --> 00:47:45.630 align:middle
The directors with casting authority are
the very select few super heavyweights

00:47:45.630 --> 00:47:49.210 align:middle
or those working on low-budget small-scale films.

00:47:49.790 --> 00:47:52.080 align:middle
So, which do I look like to you?

00:47:52.500 --> 00:47:54.960 align:middle
Uh... a super-heavyweight direct-

00:47:54.960 --> 00:47:56.750 align:middle
Swing and a miss.

00:47:56.750 --> 00:47:59.580 align:middle
We're on the set of a low-budget film here.

00:48:01.330 --> 00:48:04.830 align:middle
Director, thank you for taking care of Aqua today.

00:48:05.130 --> 00:48:08.250 align:middle
No, not at all. And we're on
the same page about that matter, right?

00:48:08.250 --> 00:48:13.000 align:middle
Er, yes... Aqua has joined
Strawberry Productions as of this month.

00:48:13.000 --> 00:48:16.420 align:middle
The thing is, there'll be hell to pay if I use
a kid who's not affiliated with an agency.

00:48:16.420 --> 00:48:20.380 align:middle
In terms of acting, I feel like my sister
is probably better than me.

00:48:20.380 --> 00:48:22.170 align:middle
Nope, it's you I want.

00:48:22.420 --> 00:48:24.580 align:middle
It's in exchange for your performance
that I'm giving Ai a part.

00:48:24.830 --> 00:48:27.380 align:middle
In the industry, we call this bartering.

00:48:27.380 --> 00:48:28.880 align:middle
It's one of the fundamentals, so keep it in mind.

00:48:30.960 --> 00:48:33.580 align:middle
Bartering Ai-san for her own son...

00:48:33.960 --> 00:48:38.250 align:middle
That stern-looking director has taken
quite a liking to you, Aqua-san.

00:48:38.670 --> 00:48:41.130 align:middle
What in the world did you do to make this happen?

00:48:41.500 --> 00:48:43.500 align:middle
Nothing all that special.

00:48:44.080 --> 00:48:48.670 align:middle
Old guys for some reason tend to enjoy it when
young people have a casual attitude with them,

00:48:48.670 --> 00:48:51.040 align:middle
so I don't act pompously toward him is all.

00:48:51.040 --> 00:48:53.080 align:middle
You're one dreadful baby...

00:48:53.580 --> 00:48:58.250 align:middle
My work saw me often interacting with seniors,
so I know how to deal with old folks.

00:48:58.580 --> 00:49:01.040 align:middle
I never thought that strange skill
would prove useful now...

00:49:01.250 --> 00:49:03.710 align:middle
Costumes

00:49:01.250 --> 00:49:03.710 align:middle
are in here

00:49:01.420 --> 00:49:06.460 align:middle
Mama! Mama! I wanna go back to Mama!

00:49:06.460 --> 00:49:08.460 align:middle
Why isn't Mama here?

00:49:08.460 --> 00:49:10.750 align:middle
Because Ai doesn't film the same days I do.

00:49:11.080 --> 00:49:13.630 align:middle
I wanna go home and snuggle up to her!

00:49:13.630 --> 00:49:15.830 align:middle
I wanna be held to Mama's breast and pampered!

00:49:15.830 --> 00:49:18.290 align:middle
Isn't she embarrassed to
be acting like that at her age?

00:49:18.290 --> 00:49:20.380 align:middle
Not that I know how old she really is inside...

00:49:23.380 --> 00:49:25.710 align:middle
This is a professional worksite, you know!

00:49:26.830 --> 00:49:29.210 align:middle
If you came to play, head home right now!

00:49:29.830 --> 00:49:31.040 align:middle
Um...

00:49:31.630 --> 00:49:34.170 align:middle
Kana Arima. I'm an actress in the film.

00:49:34.710 --> 00:49:36.330 align:middle
Oh, isn't she...?

00:49:36.830 --> 00:49:38.210 align:middle
Hmm, what was it again?

00:49:38.790 --> 00:49:41.170 align:middle
The genius child actor who can lick baking soda like that.

00:49:38.790 --> 00:49:41.920 align:middle
Baking Soda

00:49:38.790 --> 00:49:41.920 align:middle
The genius child actor who can lick baking soda like that

00:49:41.920 --> 00:49:44.210 align:middle
The genius child actor who can cry in ten seconds flat!

00:49:41.920 --> 00:49:44.420 align:middle
The much-talked about                                                       Tokyo

00:49:41.920 --> 00:49:44.420 align:middle
quick-crying child actor

00:49:41.920 --> 00:49:44.420 align:middle
Noteworthy

00:49:41.920 --> 00:49:44.420 align:middle
The genius child actor who can cry in ten seconds flat

00:49:44.710 --> 00:49:47.500 align:middle
Everybody says the way I cry in dramas is amazing!

00:49:47.790 --> 00:49:49.130 align:middle
Because it is amazing!

00:49:49.380 --> 00:49:52.170 align:middle
You know, I don't really like this girl.

00:49:52.170 --> 00:49:55.250 align:middle
Like, she seems fake, and
I have an instinctive distaste for her.

00:49:55.250 --> 00:49:58.750 align:middle
There are some people who are
unusually hard on child actors...

00:49:58.750 --> 00:49:59.880 align:middle
Like you, for example.

00:50:00.170 --> 00:50:02.960 align:middle
I know about you! You're that kid who had an in.

00:50:03.210 --> 00:50:09.710 align:middle
That Was The Start

00:50:03.380 --> 00:50:07.630 align:middle
Back when we did the script reading, you
and that idol weren't even part of the story...

00:50:07.630 --> 00:50:10.000 align:middle
Even Mama said the director forced it through!

00:50:10.210 --> 00:50:12.330 align:middle
That's simply not acceptable, okay?!

00:50:12.790 --> 00:50:14.420 align:middle
Well, that's not really...

00:50:14.420 --> 00:50:19.080 align:middle
I watched the drama the director shot recently,
and that idol hardly had any screen time at all.

00:50:21.040 --> 00:50:24.960 align:middle
I bet her acting was so horrible
they were forced to cut her parts.

00:50:25.630 --> 00:50:28.420 align:middle
Seems the one thing she's good
at is buttering people up!

00:50:28.790 --> 00:50:31.130 align:middle
Hey, AD, carry my bag.

00:50:31.130 --> 00:50:33.630 align:middle
Um, well, hold on just a minute...

00:50:33.960 --> 00:50:35.170 align:middle
Aqua...

00:50:35.460 --> 00:50:37.880 align:middle
I know, but she's just a kid...

00:50:37.880 --> 00:50:39.380 align:middle
I won't kill her.

00:50:41.880 --> 00:50:44.290 align:middle
The rough outline of the film's plot is that

00:50:44.580 --> 00:50:47.540 align:middle
a woman with zero confidence in her appearance

00:50:47.920 --> 00:50:52.670 align:middle
for some reason goes to a sketchy hospital deep
in the mountains to get plastic surgery.

00:50:50.460 --> 00:50:51.790 align:middle
Okay, let's shoot it!

00:50:51.790 --> 00:50:53.000 align:middle
Yes, sir!

00:50:53.670 --> 00:50:58.460 align:middle
We play the role of creepy children
she encounters at the entrance to that village.

00:50:59.040 --> 00:51:01.330 align:middle
Greetings, visitor.

00:51:01.670 --> 00:51:03.080 align:middle
We welcome you...

00:51:04.420 --> 00:51:07.920 align:middle
Now, please do stay for a while.

00:51:08.330 --> 00:51:13.540 align:middle
Huh? You're the reception party?

00:51:08.790 --> 00:51:12.210 align:middle
That's a genius child actor for you - she's great.

00:51:10.540 --> 00:51:12.420 align:middle
Do you have an issue with us being children?

00:51:12.920 --> 00:51:17.210 align:middle
Even if I do the same thing, it will be too terrible
to watch given the difference in ability.

00:51:17.540 --> 00:51:20.130 align:middle
Even a rank amateur like me understands that much.

00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:22.210 align:middle
So, what should I do?

00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:27.630 align:middle
Entrance to the village: creepy children turn up

00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:27.630 align:middle
Child A: "Greetings, visitor. We welcome you...

00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:27.630 align:middle
Now, please do stay for a while."

00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:27.630 align:middle
Risa: "Huh? You're the reception party?"

00:51:22.670 --> 00:51:27.630 align:middle
Child A: "Do you have an issue with us being children?"

00:51:23.080 --> 00:51:26.920 align:middle
Well, the standard answer is that
I should act like a creepy kid...

00:51:27.790 --> 00:51:30.000 align:middle
But that's not what he wants from me, is it?

00:51:30.630 --> 00:51:32.960 align:middle
The visual the director is after is surely...

00:51:34.000 --> 00:51:36.630 align:middle
There's only a single lodging in this village.

00:51:37.210 --> 00:51:40.920 align:middle
Once you check in, you might enjoy
taking a stroll around the village.

00:51:41.790 --> 00:51:44.670 align:middle
This scene is one that was added in haste...

00:51:45.000 --> 00:51:48.630 align:middle
After the director met me, he revised
the screenplay with me in mind.

00:51:49.420 --> 00:51:53.040 align:middle
If my aim is to intuit his intent,
it's actually better I don't even act.

00:51:53.790 --> 00:51:56.040 align:middle
It's sufficient if I just respond to the intent of his direction.

00:51:56.460 --> 00:52:00.540 align:middle
He never put it into words,
but what the director wants to say is...

00:52:01.880 --> 00:52:05.500 align:middle
Even without any acting, you're plenty creepy already.

00:52:06.080 --> 00:52:08.250 align:middle
Well then, if you will follow me.

00:52:14.000 --> 00:52:16.000 align:middle
Cut! That'll do!

00:52:17.250 --> 00:52:18.630 align:middle
That's good stuff.

00:52:18.630 --> 00:52:20.830 align:middle
He was just being himself, huh?

00:52:23.130 --> 00:52:26.630 align:middle
You're amazing! You sent a chill down my spine.

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:29.040 align:middle
Really? That's good to hear.

00:52:30.080 --> 00:52:31.250 align:middle
Nothing good about it.

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:35.380 align:middle
Clear out anything in that camera's frame!
We're gonna shoot the start of the next scene.

00:52:35.380 --> 00:52:36.170 align:middle
Yes, sir!

00:52:36.170 --> 00:52:38.380 align:middle
Director, reshoot the scene.

00:52:38.380 --> 00:52:40.790 align:middle
Hm? But there aren't any problems with it.

00:52:40.920 --> 00:52:42.540 align:middle
There's a huge problem!

00:52:48.420 --> 00:52:49.670 align:middle
Just now I...

00:52:50.420 --> 00:52:53.000 align:middle
wasn't nearly as good as that boy.

00:52:54.000 --> 00:52:55.880 align:middle
I can't take it! One more time!

00:52:56.210 --> 00:52:57.380 align:middle
I'm begging you!

00:52:57.380 --> 00:52:59.960 align:middle
This time I promise I'll do better!

00:53:00.790 --> 00:53:01.420 align:middle
One more time!

00:53:01.420 --> 00:53:02.290 align:middle
Kana-chan!

00:53:02.290 --> 00:53:02.830 align:middle
Please!

00:53:10.080 --> 00:53:11.000 align:middle
Hey, Precocious.

00:53:11.290 --> 00:53:14.080 align:middle
What do you think is the most
essential element for an actor?

00:53:14.710 --> 00:53:17.710 align:middle
Hmm... ability or a feel for acting?

00:53:17.710 --> 00:53:19.420 align:middle
Drive and effort?

00:53:19.420 --> 00:53:25.000 align:middle
That Was The Start

00:53:19.960 --> 00:53:22.000 align:middle
Well, that stuff is important, too.

00:53:22.500 --> 00:53:24.830 align:middle
But in the end, it's communication skills.

00:53:25.380 --> 00:53:29.250 align:middle
If fellow actors or staff take a disliking to you,
your job prospects will soon dry up.

00:53:29.880 --> 00:53:33.920 align:middle
If you get a swollen head while still young
and act like a big shot, you have no future.

00:53:34.670 --> 00:53:36.790 align:middle
Were you trying to rake her over the coals?

00:53:36.790 --> 00:53:39.750 align:middle
I wasn't thinking anything patronizing like that.

00:53:40.420 --> 00:53:42.040 align:middle
But this sort of thing is nourishment to grow.

00:53:43.330 --> 00:53:47.540 align:middle
Your acting today... was exactly how I envisioned it.

00:53:49.920 --> 00:53:54.710 align:middle
That girl was more impressive than me.
I was just being the way I always am.

00:53:54.710 --> 00:53:57.460 align:middle
Even so, I never once instructed you to do that.

00:53:57.710 --> 00:54:00.080 align:middle
Reading someone's intentions
is one part of communication skills.

00:54:00.830 --> 00:54:04.710 align:middle
Acting with an understanding of the direction
and intent is of course fundamental for an actor.

00:54:05.210 --> 00:54:09.630 align:middle
But precious is the actor who can even
read intent that can't be put into words.

00:54:10.170 --> 00:54:14.000 align:middle
After all, the correct visual is something
we directors possess in our minds.

00:54:15.920 --> 00:54:20.920 align:middle
Rather than one who does amazing acting,
become an actor who can act just as envisioned.

00:54:24.460 --> 00:54:27.630 align:middle
Er, I'm not going to become an actor...

00:54:28.460 --> 00:54:32.420 align:middle
And thus, I dipped my toes into the industry.

00:54:36.540 --> 00:54:40.250 align:middle
Creepy Child A

00:54:36.540 --> 00:54:40.250 align:middle
Creepy Child B

00:54:36.540 --> 00:54:40.250 align:middle
Kana Arima

00:54:36.540 --> 00:54:40.250 align:middle
Aqua

00:54:37.380 --> 00:54:39.880 align:middle
So he has a proper stage name...

00:54:40.830 --> 00:54:41.710 align:middle
"Aqua."

00:54:42.420 --> 00:54:43.540 align:middle
I won't forget it.

00:54:44.750 --> 00:54:46.710 align:middle
Next time, you won't get the best of me.

00:54:50.210 --> 00:54:55.540 align:middle
That Was The Start nominated for Demure Director's

00:54:50.210 --> 00:54:55.540 align:middle
Prize/Best Screenplay. Taishi Gotanda: "I want to prove

00:54:50.210 --> 00:54:55.540 align:middle
it's possible to shoot an entertaining film on a low budget."

00:54:50.630 --> 00:54:54.670 align:middle
Three years have passed since I was reborn as Ai's child.

00:54:55.290 --> 00:54:58.420 align:middle
The film the director shot was reasonably well received,

00:54:58.710 --> 00:55:01.420 align:middle
and he was nominated for the
Director's Prize at some awards ceremony.

00:55:02.040 --> 00:55:05.750 align:middle
Looking back on it, I think my acting was quite skilled.

00:55:06.710 --> 00:55:07.380 align:middle
However...

00:55:09.380 --> 00:55:13.040 align:middle
in the end it was Ai was who carried the entire film.

00:55:14.170 --> 00:55:18.380 align:middle
I don't know if that was the springboard,
but she landed a lot more work.

00:55:18.830 --> 00:55:25.330 align:middle
To sum up Ai now, she's a major up-and-coming
idol/media personality... I would venture to say.

00:55:20.080 --> 00:55:23.080 align:middle
Riveted by her

00:55:20.080 --> 00:55:23.080 align:middle
cute eyes!

00:55:20.090 --> 00:55:23.080 align:middle
Idol Group

00:55:20.090 --> 00:55:23.080 align:middle
"B Komachi"

00:55:20.090 --> 00:55:23.080 align:middle
Ai

00:55:23.080 --> 00:55:25.540 align:middle
Ai's

00:55:23.080 --> 00:55:25.540 align:middle
Prank

00:55:23.090 --> 00:55:25.540 align:middle
Successful!

00:55:26.830 --> 00:55:29.000 align:middle
Ai will soon be turning 20.

00:55:29.460 --> 00:55:34.710 align:middle
Thus far, we have been able to go about our daily lives
without being uncovered by the public.

00:55:35.960 --> 00:55:36.920 align:middle
And also...

00:55:36.920 --> 00:55:41.670 align:middle
Gorou Amemiya Doctor Disappearance

00:55:36.920 --> 00:55:41.670 align:middle
Nagoya Houmon Clinic is an environment where young

00:55:36.920 --> 00:55:41.670 align:middle
doctors can develop

00:55:36.920 --> 00:55:41.670 align:middle
Let us take young doctor Ichirou Amemiya as an example.

00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:41.130 align:middle
my corpse has not yet been found.

00:55:41.830 --> 00:55:43.830 align:middle
Hmm, you're looking cute again today!

00:55:43.830 --> 00:55:45.000 align:middle
Super cute!

00:55:45.540 --> 00:55:48.170 align:middle
Well, you're cuter overall, Mama.

00:55:48.710 --> 00:55:50.460 align:middle
What's with this rivalry?

00:55:51.210 --> 00:55:53.460 align:middle
We enrolled in a preschool.

00:55:54.000 --> 00:55:57.170 align:middle
That reminds me, what were
you doing before you were reborn?

00:55:57.170 --> 00:55:58.710 align:middle
And how old are you really, anyway?

00:55:59.290 --> 00:56:00.750 align:middle
Let's see...

00:56:02.130 --> 00:56:04.210 align:middle
If I was younger than he was...

00:56:04.580 --> 00:56:07.040 align:middle
What the heck? Should've figured you were just a kid.

00:56:07.040 --> 00:56:10.500 align:middle
From now on you better listen to everything I say, junior.

00:56:10.830 --> 00:56:14.000 align:middle
I-I'm an adult woman, okay?!

00:56:14.290 --> 00:56:17.750 align:middle
Asking about a woman's age...
What an insensitive brat you are!

00:56:18.630 --> 00:56:20.630 align:middle
Besides, who cares about my previous life?!

00:56:20.630 --> 00:56:22.170 align:middle
Quit prying!

00:56:23.000 --> 00:56:25.420 align:middle
Well, I suppose you're right.

00:56:25.960 --> 00:56:28.500 align:middle
I feel depressed whenever
I think about my previous life...

00:56:28.880 --> 00:56:32.250 align:middle
That's how much I've come to like my current life.

00:56:33.500 --> 00:56:36.460 align:middle
Compared to my days at a demanding job,

00:56:33.500 --> 00:56:35.830 align:middle
Natsuhiko Kyogoku

00:56:33.500 --> 00:56:35.830 align:middle
Jorogumo no Kotowari

00:56:36.460 --> 00:56:40.500 align:middle
as a preschooler I just eat, sleep, and read books
and such as I please - it's an easy gig.

00:56:41.830 --> 00:56:45.290 align:middle
That said, it's really something
how seriously that girl is able to play...

00:56:45.750 --> 00:56:49.330 align:middle
Huh? A preschooler is reading one
of Natsuhiko Kyogoku's tomes...

00:56:50.290 --> 00:56:54.000 align:middle
Okay, everyone, it's time for your dance routine.

00:56:54.170 --> 00:57:00.880 align:middle
Make sure to clean up

00:56:54.250 --> 00:56:58.420 align:middle
It won't be long before your families
come watch your dance...

00:56:58.420 --> 00:57:00.880 align:middle
so let's practice hard today!

00:57:01.130 --> 00:57:02.420 align:middle
Yes, ma'am!

00:57:03.330 --> 00:57:05.380 align:middle
Peach

00:57:03.540 --> 00:57:05.460 align:middle
No! I won't do it!

00:57:05.710 --> 00:57:07.250 align:middle
Ah, Ruby-chan?!

00:57:11.330 --> 00:57:12.790 align:middle
Why'd you run away?

00:57:13.670 --> 00:57:15.540 align:middle
Because I'm bad at dancing.

00:57:15.540 --> 00:57:17.250 align:middle
Or rather, I've never done it before.

00:57:17.500 --> 00:57:18.210 align:middle
Hm?

00:57:20.250 --> 00:57:22.830 align:middle
Did you always stay cooped up
in your room and play there?

00:57:22.830 --> 00:57:24.130 align:middle
Kids these days, I tell ya...

00:57:47.630 --> 00:57:49.920 align:middle
I guess I was similar to a shut-in.

00:57:49.920 --> 00:57:52.670 align:middle
I tried several times but could never do it.

00:57:53.210 --> 00:57:55.040 align:middle
I don't feel I'm capable of real exercise.

00:57:57.420 --> 00:58:01.210 align:middle
I don't know what things were like for you before...
but are you really okay with this?

00:58:02.290 --> 00:58:05.290 align:middle
You've got a long life ahead of you.

00:58:20.580 --> 00:58:22.830 align:middle
Oh? Dance practice?

00:58:24.380 --> 00:58:26.630 align:middle
How about I dance together with you?

00:58:27.250 --> 00:58:30.460 align:middle
We'll be performing an old song at
our next concert, so I've gotta practice.

00:58:41.130 --> 00:58:43.540 align:middle
Mama, your choreography is a bit off!

00:58:44.210 --> 00:58:45.080 align:middle
Huh?

00:58:45.750 --> 00:58:48.790 align:middle
At your Budokan performance, your hand was higher.

00:58:48.790 --> 00:58:52.420 align:middle
Oh? So you watched my concert video?

00:58:52.830 --> 00:58:54.710 align:middle
I'm impressed you still remember!

00:58:55.380 --> 00:58:56.420 align:middle
Of course I do.

00:58:57.540 --> 00:59:01.290 align:middle
I've seen videos of Mama's concerts hundreds...
no, thousands of times.

00:59:01.880 --> 00:59:03.790 align:middle
I remember every last bit of the choreography, too.

00:59:04.500 --> 00:59:05.580 align:middle
How'd it go again?

00:59:05.880 --> 00:59:08.420 align:middle
At this part, you went high-

00:59:09.830 --> 00:59:10.790 align:middle
You okay?

00:59:10.790 --> 00:59:11.500 align:middle
Yeah.

00:59:12.630 --> 00:59:16.830 align:middle
Ruby, with the way you move...
it's like you're ready to fall at anytime.

00:59:20.580 --> 00:59:21.500 align:middle
Well...

00:59:22.210 --> 00:59:24.040 align:middle
I was falling over all the time...

00:59:24.670 --> 00:59:27.710 align:middle
If I didn't brace myself, I'd get hurt.

00:59:33.790 --> 00:59:37.420 align:middle
If you're scared of falling over, you'll just fall even more.

00:59:38.250 --> 00:59:40.960 align:middle
Stand more confidently, with your chest out.

00:59:42.380 --> 00:59:43.750 align:middle
You'll be fine.

00:59:44.210 --> 00:59:45.540 align:middle
Trust your mama, okay?

00:59:47.880 --> 00:59:51.880 align:middle
My life came to an end with
the majority of it spent in hospital rooms.

00:59:53.630 --> 00:59:57.330 align:middle
My body was disabled, and
it mostly didn't do what I told it to.

00:59:57.830 --> 01:00:01.040 align:middle
Lying in bed, I kept longing for it so bad...

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:04.040 align:middle
Mama's cool moves...

01:00:04.420 --> 01:00:06.330 align:middle
are all etched into my brain.

01:00:07.710 --> 01:00:09.250 align:middle
All of that light...

01:00:09.960 --> 01:00:11.630 align:middle
is burned into my retinas.

01:00:12.630 --> 01:00:13.920 align:middle
O my light...

01:00:14.710 --> 01:00:16.500 align:middle
If only I could move like that...

01:00:17.330 --> 01:00:19.170 align:middle
If only I could be so free...

01:00:20.460 --> 01:00:21.170 align:middle
More!

01:00:22.380 --> 01:00:23.500 align:middle
Move more!

01:00:24.830 --> 01:00:26.540 align:middle
My body!

01:00:35.290 --> 01:00:38.290 align:middle
Ah, it's okay for me to dance, too!

01:00:42.790 --> 01:00:44.130 align:middle
So this girl...

01:00:44.540 --> 01:00:46.540 align:middle
isn't only good at acting, huh?

01:00:47.540 --> 01:00:48.880 align:middle
She has a sense for dance...

01:00:48.880 --> 01:00:51.960 align:middle
and good looks she got from our mother.

01:00:53.170 --> 01:00:55.210 align:middle
I've just had a scary thought.

01:01:01.290 --> 01:01:05.130 align:middle
On a whim, I decided to contact
the guy I'd broken up with.

01:01:05.830 --> 01:01:09.080 align:middle
You know, our kids have gotten pretty big.

01:01:09.080 --> 01:01:10.460 align:middle
Wanna try meeting them?

01:01:11.540 --> 01:01:15.250 align:middle
No, I'm not trying to get back together
or anything like that.

01:01:16.170 --> 01:01:20.040 align:middle
What led to it was overhearing
a convo the kids were having.

01:01:20.170 --> 01:01:22.630 align:middle
I try my best not to think about it...

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:26.000 align:middle
but I do wonder just who our father is.

01:01:26.920 --> 01:01:29.290 align:middle
Just thinking about it makes my heart sink.

01:01:29.290 --> 01:01:30.290 align:middle
You dummy.

01:01:30.290 --> 01:01:32.830 align:middle
You let a little thing like that get you down?

01:01:33.460 --> 01:01:35.420 align:middle
She obviously had a virgin conception, right?

01:01:35.420 --> 01:01:37.750 align:middle
There was never any guy in the first place.

01:01:38.170 --> 01:01:42.000 align:middle
She came to this odd conclusion,
and I thought, "Uh-oh, not good."

01:01:42.750 --> 01:01:47.130 align:middle
Our kids are super smart -
I'm sure they'll understand our situation.

01:01:48.380 --> 01:01:50.710 align:middle
Sure, so our new address is...

01:01:50.710 --> 01:01:51.830 align:middle
Ah, it's Ai!

01:01:53.420 --> 01:01:54.500 align:middle
Let's grab a pic!

01:01:55.170 --> 01:01:57.380 align:middle
You sure do love Ai, don't you?

01:01:57.380 --> 01:01:59.000 align:middle
My work is going well.

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:03.960 align:middle
Ai

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:03.960 align:middle
Following                                                                                     Followers

01:01:59.460 --> 01:02:01.540 align:middle
And I have over a million followers now.

01:02:01.920 --> 01:02:04.420 align:middle
The world is watching me.

01:02:05.920 --> 01:02:08.210 align:middle
Man, this is some good booze!

01:02:08.580 --> 01:02:10.170 align:middle
Come on, celebrate your new digs with a drink!

01:02:10.170 --> 01:02:11.290 align:middle
Drink up, drink up!

01:02:11.500 --> 01:02:13.630 align:middle
Wow, that's a Moriizo!

01:02:13.630 --> 01:02:14.880 align:middle
Not so fast.

01:02:14.880 --> 01:02:17.500 align:middle
Moriizo

01:02:15.210 --> 01:02:17.790 align:middle
Ai-san doesn't turn 20 until next week.

01:02:17.790 --> 01:02:19.540 align:middle
Please wait just a bit longer.

01:02:19.540 --> 01:02:22.040 align:middle
Ah, you're right - got me there!

