01:02:24.710 --> 01:02:27.580 align:middle
The TV drama Ai stars in is climbing up in the ratings!

01:02:27.580 --> 01:02:30.420 align:middle
And B Komachi's work schedule is packed, too!

01:02:30.420 --> 01:02:33.580 align:middle
Next week, we're finally performing at a dome!

01:02:34.790 --> 01:02:36.330 align:middle
He's certainly in a good mood.

01:02:36.330 --> 01:02:41.540 align:middle
Well, it was always the president's dream
to have an idol he nurtured make it to a dome.

01:02:41.790 --> 01:02:44.500 align:middle
Well, all us staff share that dream, too.

01:02:44.920 --> 01:02:46.920 align:middle
Are domes really that special?

01:02:47.170 --> 01:02:49.710 align:middle
They carry a different connotation
compared to other venues.

01:02:50.170 --> 01:02:53.710 align:middle
Moreover, you can't even book a slot without
going through a specialized company.

01:02:53.710 --> 01:02:57.540 align:middle
Merch Shop

01:02:53.710 --> 01:02:57.540 align:middle
End of line

01:02:53.960 --> 01:02:57.920 align:middle
The proficiency and track record of staff who
are able to manage a huge number of spectators...

01:02:58.170 --> 01:03:01.250 align:middle
And there's a rigorous screening process
to see if an artist is suitable for the dome.

01:03:02.290 --> 01:03:06.040 align:middle
They're venues that require a big time
commitment and lots of staff labor.

01:03:06.420 --> 01:03:08.830 align:middle
Simply having money doesn't
mean one can perform there.

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:11.830 align:middle
They're stages onto which only a chosen few can climb.

01:03:12.580 --> 01:03:14.630 align:middle
Domes are what everyone dreams of.

01:03:15.080 --> 01:03:16.330 align:middle
I see...

01:03:17.290 --> 01:03:19.630 align:middle
When I sell well, everyone is pleased.

01:03:19.920 --> 01:03:22.580 align:middle
So I'll put on the appearance of being happy, too.

01:03:22.790 --> 01:03:24.080 align:middle
This is an important period!

01:03:24.080 --> 01:03:26.040 align:middle
Be sure not to have any scandals!

01:03:26.380 --> 01:03:29.330 align:middle
Please don't try to meet up with their father, you hear?

01:03:29.630 --> 01:03:30.540 align:middle
Of course.

01:03:30.960 --> 01:03:32.330 align:middle
I'm a liar.

01:03:32.880 --> 01:03:36.080 align:middle
Before even thinking, I say whatever fits the situation.

01:03:36.500 --> 01:03:40.420 align:middle
Even I can't distinguish my real feelings from the lies.

01:03:39.670 --> 01:03:42.040 align:middle
Mama, pat me.

01:03:42.960 --> 01:03:44.250 align:middle
Pat, pat~

01:03:45.540 --> 01:03:49.080 align:middle
Since long ago, I've always
been bad at loving something.

01:03:49.670 --> 01:03:52.630 align:middle
You don't need to do anything to try to make me happy.

01:03:51.540 --> 01:03:56.250 align:middle
I'd thought I couldn't possibly be suited to be an idol.

01:03:53.790 --> 01:03:56.250 align:middle
After all, so long as you're here beside me...

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.670 align:middle
You said you were a scout, so I was wondering...

01:04:00.080 --> 01:04:02.170 align:middle
An idol? Me?

01:04:02.170 --> 01:04:03.880 align:middle
What a laugh!

01:04:04.250 --> 01:04:09.380 align:middle
My agency is just now putting together
a unit featuring middle-school models, you see.

01:04:09.380 --> 01:04:11.880 align:middle
I think you'd have a good shot at becoming the center.

01:04:12.210 --> 01:04:13.290 align:middle
Not interested.

01:04:13.290 --> 01:04:15.790 align:middle
Come on, you'd be perfect for it. I guarantee it.

01:04:17.210 --> 01:04:19.330 align:middle
I think you'd better forget all about it.

01:04:19.330 --> 01:04:21.210 align:middle
Besides, I've grown up in an children's home.

01:04:22.130 --> 01:04:26.920 align:middle
I only had a single parent from the start,
then my mom got arrested for theft when I was little.

01:04:27.250 --> 01:04:29.670 align:middle
So I was put in a home while she was away.

01:04:30.170 --> 01:04:34.630 align:middle
But, my mom never came and
picked me up after her release.

01:04:35.580 --> 01:04:39.790 align:middle
I thought if I frightened him a bit, the scout would leave.

01:04:40.250 --> 01:04:41.880 align:middle
Well, it's fine, though.

01:04:41.880 --> 01:04:44.170 align:middle
I mean, the children's home is better than getting hit.

01:04:45.210 --> 01:04:48.750 align:middle
I have no memory of ever
loving someone or being loved.

01:04:49.040 --> 01:04:51.710 align:middle
Someone like that could never be an idol, right?

01:04:52.580 --> 01:04:55.080 align:middle
The impression of idols was...

01:04:55.670 --> 01:05:00.460 align:middle
pure beings who flash smiles and
bring smiles to everyone's faces.

01:05:01.330 --> 01:05:04.380 align:middle
The polar opposite of me, a people-hating liar.

01:05:05.330 --> 01:05:08.040 align:middle
I'm sure I wouldn't be able to love the fans.

01:05:08.420 --> 01:05:09.960 align:middle
And they wouldn't love me either.

01:05:10.130 --> 01:05:11.420 align:middle
But isn't that fine?

01:05:12.630 --> 01:05:15.710 align:middle
It's not a job normal folks are suited for in the first place.

01:05:15.710 --> 01:05:17.710 align:middle
Your background gives you individuality.

01:05:17.960 --> 01:05:19.000 align:middle
B-but...

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:22.000 align:middle
Idols say stuff like "I love all of you."

01:05:22.460 --> 01:05:23.500 align:middle
If I said that, I'd be ly-

01:05:23.500 --> 01:05:24.960 align:middle
Lying is fine.

01:05:24.960 --> 01:05:28.040 align:middle
In fact, pretty lies are what fans want.

01:05:28.040 --> 01:05:30.000 align:middle
Lying is a talent, you know.

01:05:30.210 --> 01:05:32.670 align:middle
It's all good. Go on and lie up a storm!

01:05:35.460 --> 01:05:36.330 align:middle
That's really alright?

01:05:37.540 --> 01:05:39.040 align:middle
Even if it's a lie...

01:05:39.040 --> 01:05:41.210 align:middle
it's okay to say, "I love you"?

01:05:42.630 --> 01:05:45.920 align:middle
Isn't the truth that you actually do want to love people?

01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:48.420 align:middle
It's just that you don't know how.

01:05:48.920 --> 01:05:51.580 align:middle
You just never find the right object for your love.

01:05:51.960 --> 01:05:56.960 align:middle
If you sing and dance while looking cute,
that on its own is an expression of love to the fans.

01:05:57.420 --> 01:06:02.290 align:middle
If you become an idol, phrases like
"I love you" will appear all over your lyrics.

01:06:02.290 --> 01:06:08.830 align:middle
Plus, as you continue saying "I love all of you"
the lie might become the truth.

01:06:10.460 --> 01:06:13.080 align:middle
"The lie... might become the truth."

01:06:13.750 --> 01:06:17.210 align:middle
Hearing those words, I decided to become an idol.

01:06:18.460 --> 01:06:20.290 align:middle
I wanted to love someone.

01:06:20.290 --> 01:06:22.380 align:middle
I wanted an object for my love.

01:06:23.080 --> 01:06:26.420 align:middle
I thought if I became an idol, I'd be able to love my fans.

01:06:27.250 --> 01:06:30.290 align:middle
I wanted to say "I love you" and have
it come from the bottom of my heart,

01:06:30.710 --> 01:06:33.170 align:middle
so I said the lie of "I love you" all over the place.

01:06:35.460 --> 01:06:39.000 align:middle
I thought that if I became a mother,
I'd be able to love my children.

01:06:39.750 --> 01:06:43.670 align:middle
But I have not yet once told my children I love them.

01:06:44.380 --> 01:06:49.040 align:middle
If I were to utter those words
and realize I was in fact lying...

01:06:49.580 --> 01:06:51.080 align:middle
The thought of it scares me.

01:06:51.960 --> 01:06:54.420 align:middle
That's why today I will once again lie...

01:06:55.040 --> 01:06:57.420 align:middle
believing the lies will become the truth.

01:06:58.580 --> 01:07:02.170 align:middle
Even if I end up paying for it one day...

01:07:03.290 --> 01:07:05.500 align:middle
Cancel

01:07:03.290 --> 01:07:05.500 align:middle
I'm excited for today's

01:07:03.290 --> 01:07:05.500 align:middle
dome concert~~

01:07:06.920 --> 01:07:08.210 align:middle
Could that be the president and co.?

01:07:09.080 --> 01:07:10.210 align:middle
Coming!

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:15.830 align:middle
Congrats on your dome concert.

01:07:16.920 --> 01:07:18.710 align:middle
How are your twins?

01:08:09.250 --> 01:08:10.330 align:middle
Does that hurt?!

01:08:10.330 --> 01:08:10.830 align:middle
Ai!

01:08:10.830 --> 01:08:12.580 align:middle
I was hurt worse!

01:08:12.580 --> 01:08:13.790 align:middle
It was incredibly painful!

01:08:13.790 --> 01:08:16.420 align:middle
You went and had kids even though you're an idol!

01:08:16.750 --> 01:08:18.500 align:middle
You fan-betraying slut.

01:08:17.130 --> 01:08:18.500 align:middle
Ai! Ai!

01:08:18.500 --> 01:08:20.330 align:middle
You treated us fans like we didn't exist!

01:08:20.330 --> 01:08:22.460 align:middle
I bet you mocked us behind our backs!

01:08:22.460 --> 01:08:23.580 align:middle
You damn liar!

01:08:23.830 --> 01:08:26.420 align:middle
You lured us in with your constant
"I love you! I love you!" crap!

01:08:26.420 --> 01:08:28.170 align:middle
It was all lies!

01:08:28.830 --> 01:08:31.630 align:middle
I've been irresponsible from the start...

01:08:32.330 --> 01:08:36.080 align:middle
I'm not pure, and I'm dishonest and dirty.

01:08:36.540 --> 01:08:39.210 align:middle
I don't have a good grasp of
what it means love someone...

01:08:40.080 --> 01:08:41.500 align:middle
So, instead...

01:08:42.380 --> 01:08:46.790 align:middle
I told pretty lies that would please everyone...

01:08:47.290 --> 01:08:51.540 align:middle
always hoping that one day those lies
would become the truth.

01:08:52.080 --> 01:08:56.130 align:middle
I tried my best, worked hard,
and lied with everything I had.

01:08:57.040 --> 01:08:59.040 align:middle
To me, lies are love.

01:08:59.920 --> 01:09:04.080 align:middle
And in my own way, I thought I was expressing love.

01:09:04.710 --> 01:09:08.130 align:middle
I don't know if I was able to love you and the others...

01:09:08.540 --> 01:09:12.460 align:middle
but I sang all those love songs
while thinking that I wanted to.

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:17.580 align:middle
Hoping that someday that would be the truth.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:23.750 align:middle
Even now, I want to love you.

01:09:24.380 --> 01:09:25.500 align:middle
Liar...

01:09:26.080 --> 01:09:28.420 align:middle
You don't even remember me, do you?

01:09:28.790 --> 01:09:29.960 align:middle
You just want me to let you go, ri-

01:09:29.960 --> 01:09:31.500 align:middle
You're Ryousuke-kun, aren't you?

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:33.830 align:middle
You often came to the handshake events.

01:09:34.540 --> 01:09:35.920 align:middle
Oh? Am I wrong?

01:09:36.330 --> 01:09:39.960 align:middle
Sorry, I was never very good with names.

01:09:40.500 --> 01:09:44.420 align:middle
I was happy when I got that
star sand from you as a present.

01:09:45.380 --> 01:09:48.420 align:middle
I've still got it displayed in my living room.

01:09:48.960 --> 01:09:50.880 align:middle
What the hell? I...

01:09:51.290 --> 01:09:53.080 align:middle
That's not what...!

01:09:56.710 --> 01:09:58.040 align:middle
Just get over here right now!

01:10:00.210 --> 01:10:00.960 align:middle
Ai!

01:10:01.290 --> 01:10:02.630 align:middle
I've called an ambulance!

01:10:03.420 --> 01:10:05.580 align:middle
Well, I let my guard down there.

01:10:06.130 --> 01:10:09.170 align:middle
So door chains are for times like this, huh?

01:10:09.540 --> 01:10:12.710 align:middle
They never taught us that back at the home.

01:10:12.710 --> 01:10:13.670 align:middle
Don't try to speak!

01:10:13.670 --> 01:10:14.670 align:middle
The bleeding...

01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:17.130 align:middle
It's her abdominal aorta? Shit!

01:10:22.830 --> 01:10:25.500 align:middle
I'm sorry. This is probably...

01:10:26.040 --> 01:10:27.250 align:middle
it for me.

01:10:28.670 --> 01:10:29.960 align:middle
Are you alright?

01:10:30.460 --> 01:10:32.790 align:middle
You're not hurt, are you, Aqua?

01:10:33.790 --> 01:10:34.920 align:middle
No, I'm not.

01:10:38.460 --> 01:10:41.080 align:middle
I wonder if today's dome concert will be canceled...

01:10:41.790 --> 01:10:44.040 align:middle
I feel sorry for everyone.

01:10:44.580 --> 01:10:47.750 align:middle
The movie schedule had been finalized, too.

01:10:48.080 --> 01:10:50.040 align:middle
Apologize to the director for me.

01:10:50.960 --> 01:10:53.210 align:middle
Hey, what's wrong?

01:10:54.330 --> 01:10:56.170 align:middle
What's going on over there?

01:10:56.920 --> 01:10:58.880 align:middle
Stay back, Ruby.

01:11:00.170 --> 01:11:01.460 align:middle
Tell me!

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:03.040 align:middle
Ruby?

01:11:04.290 --> 01:11:08.210 align:middle
Your dance at your preschool event... was wonderful.

01:11:08.670 --> 01:11:15.330 align:middle
You know, I was thinking that maybe
you'll become an idol one day, too.

01:11:16.290 --> 01:11:18.710 align:middle
Mother and daughter performing together...

01:11:19.130 --> 01:11:20.880 align:middle
Sounds fun, doesn't it?

01:11:21.540 --> 01:11:23.420 align:middle
Aqua, will you be an actor?

01:11:24.830 --> 01:11:28.790 align:middle
I wonder... what kind of adults you'll grow up to be...

01:11:29.960 --> 01:11:34.130 align:middle
Aw, I'd like to see you with your school backpacks...

01:11:34.710 --> 01:11:36.880 align:middle
And on parents' day...

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:40.830 align:middle
I want people to say, "Isn't she
a bit young to be Ruby's mother?"

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:47.080 align:middle
As the two of you grow up... I want to be there to see it.

01:11:48.790 --> 01:11:51.750 align:middle
Not that I was the best mom or anything...

01:11:52.540 --> 01:11:56.210 align:middle
but I'm glad I gave birth to you.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:11:58.670 align:middle
And, also...

01:11:58.670 --> 01:12:01.290 align:middle
Ah, I gotta tell you this.

01:12:02.880 --> 01:12:03.750 align:middle
Ruby...

01:12:04.670 --> 01:12:05.790 align:middle
Aqua...

01:12:07.170 --> 01:12:08.290 align:middle
I love you.

01:12:10.250 --> 01:12:13.080 align:middle
Ah, I was finally able to say it.

01:12:13.960 --> 01:12:17.420 align:middle
I'm sorry... it took me so long.

01:12:18.460 --> 01:12:19.880 align:middle
I'm so relieved.

01:12:20.580 --> 01:12:24.830 align:middle
Those words definitely weren't a lie.

01:12:29.710 --> 01:12:30.630 align:middle
Ai...?

01:12:40.960 --> 01:12:42.040 align:middle
